==English==

===Noun===
'''sari'''

#A length of [[fabric]] wound around the body of [[Hindu]] women. It is an outer garment worn by a woman consisting of a single length of [[cotton]] or [[silk]], 5 to 7 yards long, most often with one end wrapped around the waist to form a skirt, the other draped over the shoulder, or head. This is the traditional dress of women in the [[Indian Subcontinent]]

